## 10. Schema evolution — backwards compat

### 10.1. Additive changes (без bump)

OK без version bump:
- Adding new optional fields в response
- Adding new optional query params
- Adding new endpoints
- Adding new enum values (если frontend tolerates unknown)

### 10.2. Breaking changes (требуют bump)

Требуют major version bump:
- Removing fields
- Renaming fields
- Changing field types
- Making optional → required
- Removing endpoints

### 10.3. Deprecation discipline

```http
GET /v1/old-endpoint
Response:
Deprecation: Sun, 11 Nov 2026 23:59:59 GMT
Sunset: Sun, 11 Nov 2027 23:59:59 GMT
Link: <https://docs.example.com/migrations/v2>; rel="deprecation"
```

- **Deprecation** header — when deprecated
- **Sunset** header — when removed (≥ 6 months later typically)
- **Link** к migration guide
- Email / dashboard notification к API consumers

### 10.4. Version negotiation

URI versioning (`/v1/`, `/v2/`) — параллельные versions on infra during transition.

Date header versioning (Stripe) — client pin'ит version, server adapts response.

Choose one approach project-wide.

