## 11. Observability outward

### 11.1. Каждый endpoint в metrics

- **Request rate** (req/s)
- **Latency** (p50 / p95 / p99) per endpoint
- **Error rate** (per status code)
- **Saturation** (DB pool / CPU / memory)

Standard libs: Prometheus / OpenTelemetry / Datadog.

### 11.2. Status page

- Public status page (statuspage.io / instatus / self-hosted)
- Real-time health per service / endpoint
- Incident history + post-mortems link

### 11.3. Health endpoints

```
GET /healthz       — liveness (process up)
GET /readyz        — readiness (готов serve traffic)
GET /version       — build SHA / version
```

Не expose'ить sensitive info — только operational signals.

### 11.4. Structured logs

- JSON / logfmt format
- Включают: timestamp, request_id, user_id, endpoint, latency_ms, status
- `request_id` propagation через distributed trace (W3C Trace Context)

### 11.5. Error tracking

- Sentry / Rollbar / Honeybadger для exceptions
- Не log sensitive data (PII / secrets) — sanitize before sending

---

## 12. Discoverability + DX (developer experience)

### 12.1. API spec обязателен

- **OpenAPI 3.x** (REST) — single source of truth для schema
- **AsyncAPI** (WebSocket / SSE / message brokers)
- **GraphQL SDL** (если GraphQL)
- **Protobuf** (если gRPC)

### 12.2. Generated artifacts из spec

- **Client SDK** (typed bindings для каждого supported language)
- **API reference docs** (Redoc / Stoplight / Swagger UI)
- **Postman / Insomnia collection**
- **Mock server** для frontend dev

### 12.3. Examples в docs

- **Curl command** для каждого endpoint
- **Real-world use case** (не «hello world»)
- **Error response examples** — все 4xx / 5xx variants
- **Idempotency / pagination / rate limiting** — explicit examples

### 12.4. Sandbox / test mode

- Отдельный environment (`api.test.example.com` или test API key)
- Mock external dependencies (payments, sms)
- Reset endpoint для clean state

### 12.5. Changelog

- `/v1/changelog` или GitHub release notes
- Каждое release — что добавлено / изменено / deprecated
- Email subscription для API consumers

---

## 13. Security baseline

### 13.1. Transport

- **TLS 1.3** primary (1.2 fallback) — `--tls-min-version` enforced
- **HSTS** header — `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains`
- **Certificate pinning** для mobile (опционально, careful с rotation)

### 13.2. CORS

- Whitelist explicit origins (никаких `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` для authenticated APIs)
- Preflight handling корректный
- `credentials: include` — только для same-org domains

### 13.3. Input validation

- Validation **на server side** обязательно (frontend validation = UX nicety, не security)
- Whitelist > blacklist (allowed values, не «known bad»)
- Size limits для всех string fields, body, file uploads

### 13.4. Secrets — никогда в response

- Никогда не возвращать password hashes, API keys, internal tokens в response body
- PII fields — explicit «include» query param (`?include=email`) с access check

### 13.5. Audit log

- Auth events (login / logout / password change / 2FA setup)
- Sensitive data access (read of PII)
- Admin actions
- Retention соответствует regulatory requirements

